Parliament, Tuesday, 19 November 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Defence and Military Veterans will tomorrow be briefed by the Department of Defence (DOD) on its cyber-warfare capabilities and developments. The committee will also be briefed on the Military Discipline Bill [B 21 – 2019]. The Bill seeks to provide, amongst others, for an effective administration of the military justice system and maintenance of discipline in the Defence Force. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 20 November 2019
	Time: 10:00 am
	Venue: Committee Room M314, Third Floor, Marks Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON DEFENCE AND MILITARY VETERANS, MR CYRIL XABA. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Felicia Lombard (Ms)
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 063 503 2364
	E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za The annual Budget determines how much money government departments will receive and has to be approved by Parliament.Read more